Description:
Beautifully Updated Townhouse on Own Title
Recently updated and painted throughout within the last twelve months, this stylish single level brick townhouse is ideal for the first home buyer, downsizer or astute investor alike. Featuring 3 generous bedrooms, the master with walk-in robe and built-in robes to the other 2 and serviced by an updated central family bathroom. The home boasts 2 living zones comprising an open plan living, dining and kitchen area and a separate lounge room. Step outside through the sliding glass doors to a very private courtyard.
Features include: quality appliances and stone bench top in the kitchen, new timber laminate flooring, updated separate laundry, ducted gas central heating, split system heating and cooling, single remote garage with internal access for added security.
Corner the market with this great home on its own title and situated on a 300m2 (approx.) allotment with well-maintained front and back gardens.
This home represents outstanding value, set in a quiet street surrounded by quality homes and all of East Geelong's great amenities, including local primary and secondary schools, Garden Street shopping & cafes, local restaurants, public transport, South Geelong Railway Station and sporting facilities.
Don't miss your chance to secure this charming home, call today!

Description:
Charm, Style And Convenience, In A Fantastic Location
Set on a low maintenance block, featuring a sophisticated renovation, this stunning family cottage is a charming blend of original and new. Privately tucked away on one of East Geelong's quietest streets, this home will capture your eye from the moment you step through the door.
A wide entry hall with refurbished timber floorboards and impressive high ceilings is a perfect introduction to the exquisite style within. The home showcases a combination of old meeting new, with frosted double doors opening up to the light filled open plan kitchen, dining and living area. The well-equipped kitchen featuring stainless steel appliances, gas stove top, stone bench tops and an abundance of storage.
With bi-fold stacker doors that seamlessly adjoin the dining room to the backyard, you can sit back and relax on the private outdoor deck, the perfect spot for a cup of tea or entertaining family and friends.
Admire the elegant design showcased throughout the sitting room as you overlook the beautiful established front garden through leadlight windows. Original features include an ornamental fireplace, whilst the art deco features throughout capture the charm of the home.
The stylish interior is highlighted by its delightfully updated bathroom with floor-to-ceiling marble tiles and a large walk in frameless shower.
Consisting of 3 generous sized bedrooms, each with BIR's.
In a highly desired location of East Geelong, this gorgeous home oozes charm and character. Be prepared to fall in love the moment you walk through the front door.
Other features include:
- Gas ducted heating
- Split system cooling
- European laundry
- Secure off street parking.

Address: 6 Ranken Lane St Albans Park VIC 3219
Description:
OVER 1000m2 THERE IS ROOM TO GROW
This two story family home set on whopping 1040m2 block will impress. Located in a quiet court this 4 bed, plus study, 2.5 bath, 3 living home can be enjoyed now with room to grow.
Comprising of downstairs front bedroom with bay window and handy powder room, plus a spacious formal L shaped living room which flows beautifully onto the rear open plan kitchen/ meals area.
The kitchen is light filled and offers SS appliances, gas cooking, Bosch dishwasher and ample storage. The informal meals area comfortably seats 8 - 10 and has room for a third small sitting area offering views out to the huge rear yard.
Upstairs being freshly painted and carpeted throughout and
comprises of a spacious rumpus room and separate study/office with built in shelving. There is also 2 good sized bedrooms with BIR and a fully updated luxe two way bathroom with separate shower, heat lamps and a handy second toilet.
The Master suite is roomy and offers WIR, ensuite with spa bath, separate shower and a 3rd wc.
Outside you will find a huge back yard with views to rear parklands. There is also excellent shedding facilities with a 5x9mt shed to one side, and a double garage for extra parking on the other side.
What is rare about this property is the handy side storage space ready to house your caravan, boat, trailer or truck with no clearance restrictions.
Ideally located in growing St Albans Park only 3km from Geelong CBD and minutes drive to sporting complex, shops and parklands.
FEATURES
Braemar Ducted Gas Heating
AC
Caravan Space
New curtains and blinds
Rent approx $550pw

Description:
Peppercorn 3.03ha 7.5acres approx.
If you have been looking for a lifestyle change then look no further!
This superbly positioned country holding, in the sought after Gnarwarre area, blends an outstanding rural lifestyle while located within easy access to Geelong and the Surf Coast.
Situated on approximately 7.5 acres with two road frontages onto Heaths Road and Barrabool Road, the refurbished and modernised brick home is surrounded by beautiful gardens and established trees.
Comprising five generous sized bedrooms, master with walk in robe and ensuite, timber kitchen, lounge/dining with split system, central bathroom, laundry, study and double remote garage with internal access.
Further features include a massive family/living room with built in bar, split system and bi-fold doors that open onto the huge outdoor alfresco area.
Externally there is a three bay machinery shed/workshop with separate toilet, horse stable with tack room and storage shed, garden shed, chook shed, dam and approximately 70,000 litres of tank water.
With easy access to Highton Village, Waurn Ponds shopping centre, Geelong secondary and primary schools, Geelong CBD, Surf Coast and Melbourne CBD via the Ring Road, this exceptional property will tick all the boxes for the demanding and selective family seeking the ultimate in country lifestyle.
Terms: 10% Deposit 60 Day Settlement

Description:
Period Charm in Prized Location
With its attractive street presence and quaint period appeal, this charming weatherboard home presents delightful living for today with plenty of scope for the future. This exquisite home comprises of floorboards and neat updates throughout, while keeping its original charm.
Including, 3 bedrooms all with BIRs and with the added bonus of a 4th bedroom/home office located within the garage, with its own private bathroom. An updated central bathroom services the rest of the home.
The first of 2 living areas is located separately from the rest of the home and would suit perfectly as a rumpus room or formal living.
Further on, a large kitchen with 900mm oven, 5-burner gas stove, dishwasher and good bench space.
The dining area is located adjacent to the kitchen and 2nd living area, which leads out, via French doors to the entertainer's deck, perfect for entertaining guests.

- High ceilings
The home is perfectly complemented by a grassy yard and established gardens as well as a double garage with rear lane access and lots of storage.
Enjoy a privileged position within walking distance to the Garden St Shops, train station as well as a short distance to the waterfront and botanical gardens. Beautifully presented and utterly adorable, this is one not to miss!

Nothing To Do; Move In Or Rent Out, The Choice Is Yours!
With an estimated rental return of $340 a week and nothing to do except find the right tenants to treat it with the respect that it deserves this outstanding home is a must see inspection. Set on a spacious allotment of approx 535 square metres and tastefully updated, the home features 3 good sized bedrooms; master with built-in robes, large living area that greets you upon entry and an intelligently designed kitchen and meals area with gas cook top and plenty of storage and bench space.
Standout features include a fresh coat of paint throughout, new carpet and flooring, newly installed shower screen in the bathroom, air conditioner and gas heating in the living room and an abundance of natural light that flows through the home. All of this only minutes from the C.B.D and all that Newcomb has to offer including 2 major shopping centres, Splashdown and Primary and Secondary schools.
There's plenty of parking available in the quiet court plus space for 2 cars in the car port that leads through to easy access to the private and low maintenance rear yard. For those that require public transport there's bus stops located nearby for extra convenience.
With the infrastructure planned for Newcomb and the nearby salt works in the future there's no doubt that this property is one that you can't afford to miss, set and forget and plan for tomorrow while being rewarded today!

Description:
Custom designed living in the heart of Thomson.
This central location on offer in Thomson demands attention with schools, shopping centres, sporting reserves, the CBD, Eastern Gardens, Barwon River, Waterfront, Geelong Showgrounds, the Bellarine rail trail and train station within just minutes.
Positioned in a quiet, low traffic street in an established neighbourhood and on its own 347m2 title, this property offers peace, privacy and very low maintenance for the downsizer, 1st home buyer or wise investor.
Tiled throughout and with high ceilings, the spacious open plan design offers plenty of natural light and comprises 3 bedrooms, bathroom, premium kitchen, large living / meals area, powder room and laundry.
The spacious living/TV area is set up for home entertainment and opens to the North through sliding doors.
The huge kitchen is the crowning jewel of this property and is loaded with features including wide stone bench tops with waterfall edge, dishwasher, 900mm gas cooking, double oven, double fridge cavity, pantry, loads of storage and breakfast bar.
The 4m x 4.2m master bedroom is a great size, is carpeted and includes a full wall of floor to ceiling robes.The main bathroom boasts wall and floor tiles, large shower, a corner spa bath and is adjacent to the separate powder room.
There is also plenty of floor to ceiling linen storage cupboards.
Ducted heating, RC/AC and a team of high end ceiling fans control the climate year round.
An oversized single garage with remote roller provides secure parking and additional room for work shop or storage and the independent title means that the driveway accommodates for up to another 4 cars off street.
A garden shed, clothes line, provisions for a water tank and concrete path around the house creates an extremely low maintenance property ready for the new owners.
Call Dion to learn more and book an appointment today.

This house has been the centre for generations of the same family over 4 decades. It was last sold and purchased in 1974 by a young man as a surprise for his new wife after the arrival of their first child - and became the cornerstone of the family they built together in the years since, right up to now. The original almost 100 year old home has been renovated and extended twice during the 80s to extend the kitchen and add a large laundry accommodating a growing family - but it has retained much of the character of the original weatherboard cottage home. The 12 foot ceilings and high roofline provide spaciousness to the interior which only needs someone with an eye for possibility to come in and create something wonderful from this well-loved family home. Whilst it's not restricted by Heritage Overlay, the surrounding area is known for the retention of original character homes during renovation - and this home is the last in the block to need a renovator's touch to bring it back to life and recreate the charm of the original features as well as attending to the quirks and wrinkles that age bring. The home is located in a very family oriented area with a number of schools close by, a short walk to local shops and cafes, and the neighbourhood feeling abounds in the area. Revive and restore this charming old home and create your own family history here.
• 3 large bedrooms
• Light filled lounge room with gas heater and original mantle
• Spacious kitchen with loads of potential
• Adjoining meals area with gas wall heater
• Central bathroom
• Separate toilet
• Oversized laundry room with plenty of storage
• Double lock up garage
• Lane access to backyard via Anderson Street
• Workshop
• 400m2 block

Description:
Vintage Chic, Modern Stunner
Setting the scene for relaxed family living, this gorgeous character home blends classic and designer features to offer luxurious and carefree living in a vibrant location.
Positioned in the warmth of an established area, the ready-to-enjoy property enjoys a convenient lifestyle location close to the Garden Street cafe and shopping strip, public transport, the Botanic Gardens and the stunning Geelong Waterfront.
Step through the front door of this white weatherboard and a light-filled interior highlights stunning preserved period features which perfectly complement the modern open-plan dining, kitchen and living space.
The peaceful front section of the heritage home boasts extravagant approach to detail including soaring ceilings with timber paneling and polished timber floorboards. Here three luxuriously-appointed bedrooms with plush carpet and two with original fireplaces share a sparkling bathroom with modern freestanding bath and walk-in shower.
At the end of the hallway, a huge set of French doors shed light on the open-plan kitchen and casual meals area and offer seamless indoor-outdoor living through to the show-stopping, fully-landscaped gardens.
The kitchen truly is the heart of the home with modern stainless-steel appliances, designer light-fittings and stunning stone benchtops overlooking the alfresco meals area complete with built-in bench seating, separate fire-pit space for those chilly winter nights and secure play-zone for the kids.
Other highlights include split system heating and cooling, laundry with plenty of storage, mature fruit trees and double remote garage with rear-lane access.

Description:
Enchanting Home / Outstanding Location
Quietly tucked away in the heart of East Geelong, exuding character and charm throughout. This quaint home allows you to move in with absolute ease, yet would respond exceptionally well to a modern transformation. You will enjoy the most privileged lifestyle being only moments from all of the action of the Garden Street Shopping Precinct, South Geelong Train Station and the Geelong CBD.
Enter into the comfortable open plan living and dining area capturing fantastic natural light. Accompanying is the central kitchen, well equipped with ample cupboard space and stainless steel appliances.
Entertaining will be made easy with the expansive undercover decking, allowing for all year-round use with complete privacy. This overlooks the neat and tidy landscaped backyard for kids and pets.
Completing the home is three spacious bedrooms, two with BIR's and one with direct access out onto the deck. The main bathroom has received a modern update and is well positioned to service the home.
Features:
- Ducted Heating
- Secure off-street parking space.
- Split System A/C
- Ceiling Fans
Take advantage of a very exciting opportunity to enter the East Geelong market.
